12/04/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Two soldiers died on Saturday (April 11th) in clashes with members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) in Sirnak province in southeast Turkey, the army announced.
Immediately after the fighting, troops killed at least seven terrorists in a follow-up operation, the army added.
Meanwhile, Turkish Interior Minister Besir Atalay left for Baghdad on Saturday to take part in a meeting within the trilateral mechanism for fighting terrorism established by Turkey, Iraq and the United States in November last year.
Iraqi National Security Minister Sirvan al Vaili and US Ambassador to Baghdad Christopher Hill will also attend.
Atalay said that he expects more active measures from Iraq in the fight against the PKK.
(RIA Novosti, Anadolu news agency, Xinhua - 11/04/09)
